{"type":"message","id":"32fbf161","parentId":"f3016c8e","timestamp":"2026-03-02T06:10:28.177Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_fcdbac97e0134cf2a2a624cc","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"206:  <Step title=\"Allow responses without @mention\">\n207:    By default, your agent only responds in guild channels when @mentioned. For a private server, you probably want it to respond to every message.\n211:        > \"Allow my agent to respond on this server without having to be @mentioned\"\n292:- Select types: `string`, `user`, `role`, `mentionable`, `channel`\n388:    - `<@id>` mention\n440:    Guild messages are mention-gated by default.\n444:    - explicit bot mention\n445:    - configured mention patterns (`agents.list[].groupChat.mentionPatterns`, fallback `messages.groupChat.mentionPatterns`)\n982:    - verify `requireMention` behavior and mention patterns\n994:  <Accordion title=\"Require mention false but still blocked\">\n1021:    If you set `channels.discord.allowBots=true`, use strict mention and allowlist rules to avoid loop behavior."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":15,"aggregated":"206:  <Step title=\"Allow responses without @mention\">\n207:    By default, your agent only responds in guild channels when @mentioned. For a private server, you probably want it to respond to every message.\n211:        > \"Allow my agent to respond on this server without having to be @mentioned\"\n292:- Select types: `string`, `user`, `role`, `mentionable`, `channel`\n388:    - `<@id>` mention\n440:    Guild messages are mention-gated by default.\n444:    - explicit bot mention\n445:    - configured mention patterns (`agents.list[].groupChat.mentionPatterns`, fallback `messages.groupChat.mentionPatterns`)\n982:    - verify `requireMention` behavior and mention patterns\n994:  <Accordion title=\"Require mention false but still blocked\">\n1021:    If you set `channels.discord.allowBots=true`, use strict mention and allowlist rules to avoid loop behavior.","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772431828173}}
{"type":"message","id":"7897533a","parentId":"32fbf161","timestamp":"2026-03-02T06:10:31.692Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I found it! Let me read lines 206-220 to see how to allow responses without @mention.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f3de6e0db9cb4f08b3a587c1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/discord.md","offset":200,"limit":50}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"zai","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":295,"output":58,"cacheRead":21824,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":22177,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772431828177}}
{"type":"message","id":"26c4256c","parentId":"7897533a","timestamp":"2026-03-02T06:10:31.701Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_f3de6e0db9cb4f08b3a587c1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n      </Tab>\n    </Tabs>\n\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step title=\"Allow responses without @mention\">\n    By default, your agent only responds in guild channels when @mentioned. For a private server, you probably want it to respond to every message.\n\n    <Tabs>\n      <Tab title=\"Ask your agent\">\n        > \"Allow my agent to respond on this server without having to be @mentioned\"\n      </Tab>\n      <Tab title=\"Config\">\n        Set `requireMention: false` in your guild config:\n\n```json5\n{\n  channels: {\n    discord: {\n      guilds: {\n        YOUR_SERVER_ID: {\n          requireMention: false,\n        },\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n      </Tab>\n    </Tabs>\n\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step title=\"Plan for memory in guild channels\">\n    By default, long-term memory (MEMORY.md) only loads in DM sessions. Guild channels do not auto-load MEMORY.md.\n\n    <Tabs>\n      <Tab title=\"Ask your agent\">\n        > \"When I ask questions in Discord channels, use memory_search or memory_get if you need long-term context from MEMORY.md.\"\n      </Tab>\n      <Tab title=\"Manual\">\n        If you need shared context in every channel, put the stable instructions in `AGENTS.md` or `USER.md` (they are injected for every session). Keep long-term notes in `MEMORY.md` and access them on demand with memory tools.\n      </Tab>\n    </Tabs>\n\n  </Step>\n</Steps>\n\n\n[822 more lines in file. Use offset=250 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772431831697}}
